title: Sydney's Circular Quay set for revamp
text:
Sydney's Circular Quay set for revamp Last updated 15:25, September 28 2015 Sydney Morning Herald 
An animation of the proposed new look for Circular Quay. Vision NSW Government. 
Sydney's Circular Quay is getting a A$200 million (NZ$220 million) makeover in a bid to modernise the place once crowned the 'jewel of Sydney Harbour'. 
A new video has been released showing what the upgrade will look like. 
NSW Transport Minister Andrew Constance told Sky News , the area which sits between the Sydney Harbour Bridge and the Opera House, isn't reaching its full potential. Supplied 
A new video has been released showing what the upgrade to Sydney's Circular Quay will look like. 
'Circular Quay should be a window to our beautiful harbour but after years of neglect, this gateway to the city is simply not up to scratch,' Mr Constance said in a statement. 
The Circular Quay's makeover is expected to start in 2019.
